  "prompt": "How do I make Pani puri chutney in Tamil Nadu style?",
  "response": "Here's a recipe for Pani Puri Chutney (Pudina Chutney) in Tamil Nadu style:\n\nIngredients:\n1. Fresh mint leaves\n2. Fresh coriander leaves\n3. Green chilies\n4. Ginger\n5. Tamarind\n6. Jaggery\n7. Salt\n8. Cumin powder\n9. Black salt (optional)\n10. Water\n\nSteps:\n1. Wash mint and coriander leaves thoroughly\n\n2. Grind together:\n- Mint leaves\n- Coriander leaves\n- Green chilies\n- Ginger\n- Small piece of tamarind\n- Jaggery\n- Salt\n- Cumin powder\n- Black salt\n\n3. Add water to adjust consistency - should be thin and watery\n\n4. Strain the mixture to remove any solid pieces\n\n5. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed\n\n6. Refrigerate before serving\n\nTips:\n- Use fresh ingredients\n- Balance sweet, sour, and spicy flavors\n- Adjust green chilies according to your spice tolerance\n- Can store in refrigerator for 2-3 days\n\nServe chilled with crispy pani puris for authentic Tamil Nadu style street food experience!",
